post_text:
It is that time! Time to attend Plattsmouth Adult Education
classes. GED preparation, English classes, job search techniques or improvement of basic academics are regularly offered. This could be your time to advance your own education goals.

For more information, call Program Director Tallie VanWesten at 402-296-3174 ext. 2315, or just attend a class.

You may enroll during any regular class session: Mondays, Tuesdays, and Thursdays at 9:30 a.m. or 6:30 p.m. The classes are held in the First Presbyterian Church's lower building, The church is located at 701 Chicago Avenue, Plattsmouth.

All serious students are welcome. An individual learning plan will be developed toward each student's specific goals. Get started now. It is that time!

post_text:
We enroll every Monday at 9:15 a.m. and 6:15 p.m. in our new digs at First Presbyterian Church, 701 Chicago Avenue, Plattsmouth.

We teach all the skills needed to earn a GED. We teach English as a Second Language. If you are an adult who needs to polish some forgotten math, language, reading, writing, social studies, or science skills, you are welcome too.

We will design a program specific to you. We will stick with you until you reach your educational goals.
